cvs.texi(,14609) @node Credits
cvs.texi(,14610) @appendix Credits
cvs.texi(,14611) 
cvs.texi(,14612) @cindex Contributors (manual)
cvs.texi(,14613) @cindex Credits (manual)
cvs.texi(,14614) Roland Pesch, then of Cygnus Support <@t{roland@@wrs.com}>
cvs.texi(,14615) wrote the manual pages which were distributed with
cvs.texi(,14616) @sc{cvs} 1.3.  Much of their text was copied into this
cvs.texi(,14617) manual.  He also read an early draft
cvs.texi(,14618) of this manual and contributed many ideas and
cvs.texi(,14619) corrections.
cvs.texi(,14620) 
cvs.texi(,14621) The mailing-list @code{info-cvs} is sometimes
cvs.texi(,14622) informative. I have included information from postings
cvs.texi(,14623) made by the following persons:
cvs.texi(,14624) David G. Grubbs <@t{dgg@@think.com}>.
cvs.texi(,14625) 
cvs.texi(,14626) Some text has been extracted from the man pages for
cvs.texi(,14627) @sc{rcs}.
cvs.texi(,14628) 
cvs.texi(,14629) The @sc{cvs} @sc{faq} by David G. Grubbs has provided
cvs.texi(,14630) useful material.  The @sc{faq} is no longer maintained,
cvs.texi(,14631) however, and this manual is about the closest thing there
cvs.texi(,14632) is to a successor (with respect to documenting how to
cvs.texi(,14633) use @sc{cvs}, at least).
cvs.texi(,14634) 
cvs.texi(,14635) In addition, the following persons have helped by
cvs.texi(,14636) telling me about mistakes I've made:
cvs.texi(,14637) 
